S: Peaches, grapefruits, tangerines, and a slight dankness
T: All of the juicy tropical fruits we've come to expect with the hazy NE IPAs - pineapple, calamansi, mangoes, and oranges - capped by a crisp and dry crackery malt finish
F: Full body with moderate carbonation
O: Finally. Finally North Carolina has the hazy, juicy IPA it deserves. Man, I've longed for this day and Citraquench'l flat out delivered. From the tropical and citrusy nose to the juicy and flavorful taste profile, which was all underpinned by the thick mouthfeel, I'm delighted to report this beer is the real deal and capable of going toe to toe with some of the best that Tree House, Trillium, Tired Hands, Grimm etc. have to offer. Overall I thoroughly enjoyed this one and applaud Heist for producing a world class hazy juice bomb! Delicious. 1,004 charactersFireman_RK, Jul 14, 2016
